# creative / threejs

Three.js is the dominant JS WebGL/WebGPU 3D library. The deliverable is an interactive HTML canvas driven by JS — embeddable in a single HTML file via a CDN importmap (zero build). Static and self-animating scenes render in the universal HTML shell; offline PNG capture is done with headless Chrome (Puppeteer).

controls do
  creative.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
  creative.bg: { label: "Background color", type: "color" }
  creative.cube_color: { label: "Mesh color", type: "color" }
  creative.fov: { label: "Camera FOV", type: "range", min: "20", max: "120", step: "1" }
  creative.width: { label: "Canvas width", type: "range", min: "256", max: "1920", step: "16" }
  creative.height: { label: "Canvas height", type: "range", min: "256", max: "1080", step: "16" }
  creative.controls: { label: "OrbitControls", type: "toggle" }
  creative.animate: { label: "Animation loop", type: "toggle" }
  creative.antialias: { label: "Antialias", type: "toggle" }
end

