## Render
```bash
# zero-build: just open the generated scene in a browser
open out/scene.html   # or serve: python3 -m http.server

# headless PNG capture (optional)
npm install puppeteer three
node -e "const p=require('puppeteer');(async()=>{const b=await p.launch({headless:'new',args:['--use-gl=angle','--enable-unsafe-swiftshader']});const pg=await b.newPage();await pg.goto('file://'+process.cwd()+'/out/scene.html');await new Promise(r=>setTimeout(r,1500));await pg.screenshot({path:'out/scene.png'});await b.close();})()"
```

## Failure modes
- Blank canvas: importmap URL/version mismatch — keep the `three` import specifier and CDN version in sync.
- Headless screenshot is black: no GPU — pass `--use-gl=angle --enable-unsafe-swiftshader`; bump the settle delay above 1500ms for heavy scenes.
- `file://` module/CORS errors when loading GLTF: serve over http (`python3 -m http.server`) instead of opening the file directly.
- WebGPU renderer falls back to WebGL on browsers without WebGPU; use `WebGPURenderer` from `three/addons/` only when targeting Chrome 113+.
